eu.smartdatalake.simsearch.pivoting

Class PivotSelector

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.smartdatalake.simsearch.pivoting.PivotSelector

  • public class PivotSelector
extends Object
    Selects reference points (a.k.a. pivots) among a given collection for a specific attribute using a distance.

      • chooseByMinimalError

        private Point chooseByMinimalError(double edge)
        From a collection of points, pick the one that minimizes the error from the edge specified by the two first foci.
        Parameters:
        edge - Distance between the first two foci (pivots) already chosen.
        Returns:
        A point in the collection to become the next chosen foci (pivot).

      • embed

        public double[][] embed(int n)
        Implements the Hull of Foci algorithm and selects n reference points from the convex hull of the given collection of multi-dimensional points.
        Parameters:
        n - Number of reference points (pivots) to choose.
        Returns:
        An array that, for each point in the data collection and each of the n chosen reference points, reports their distance.

      • getPivots
